Definition: arising from or marked by despair or loss of hope
Example: a despairing view of the world situation; the last despairing plea of the condemned criminal; a desperate cry for help; helpless and desperate--as if at the end of his tether; her desperate screams
Synonyms: desperate, arising, from, or, marked, by, despair, loss, of, hope, a, view, the, world, situation, last, plea, condemned, criminal, cry, for, help, helpless, and, desperate--as, if, at, end, his, tether, her, screams
Category: adj.all
